sp.p:
His word is more than the miraculous
harp;
he hath raised the wall and houses too.

I'll swear upon that bottle to be thy
true subject;
for the liquor is not earthly.

The sound is going away;
let's follow
it, and after do our work.

Lead, monster;
we'll follow. I would
I could see this taborer;
he lays it on.

Monster, I do smell all horse-piss;
at which
my nose is in great indignation.
